HEADWORD: leprechaun
<hw>leprechaun</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Irish folklore)</fld> <def>A
small mischevous elf or spirit in Irish folklore; it is often depicted
in literature as a dwarfish bearded old man; -- legend tells that if a
leprechaun is captured, he will reveal the location of his hidden pot of
gold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

